<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="361" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="361">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">Male</emphasis>
. Body length 8-17 mm. Head and mesosoma (including legs) brown; metasoma black, 1st segment entirely and S2-S7 lighter; flagellomeres light brown; fore wing hyaline, with brown veins. Head with prolonged temples, weakly convergent behind eyes; distance between posterior ocellus and posterior head margin longer than longitudinal posterior ocellus diameter; POD 2.1-2.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
OOD; F1 slightly shorter than F2 (0.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
); basal lower mandibular tooth significantly bent downwards, distance between apex of lower tooth and upper mandibular ridge slightly longer than mandibular height at the base (see fig. 30 (8) in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, AS" journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" refId="B25" refString="Lelej, AS, 1985. The Velvet Ants (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae) of the USSR and Neighbouring Countries. Nauka, Leningrad" title="The Velvet Ants (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae) of the USSR and Neighbouring Countries." year="1985">Lelej 1985</bibRefCitation>
); S2 with well developed median basal tubercle; T2 basally and laterally with small dense foveae, becoming sparse on disc (several diameters distance apart); cuspis of volsella narrow at tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Male genitalia A, B Pseudophotopsis subaurea sp. nov., dorsal and ventral views, respectively C, D P. binghami Bischoff, dorsal and ventral views, respectively (modified from Lelej (1985))." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.82.65252.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/537916" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">35D</figureCitation>
); parapenial lobe slightly oblique inward, with broadly rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Male genitalia A, B Pseudophotopsis subaurea sp. nov., dorsal and ventral views, respectively C, D P. binghami Bischoff, dorsal and ventral views, respectively (modified from Lelej (1985))." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.82.65252.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/537916" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">35C</figureCitation>
); genital ventral lobe rather cylindrical, extending directly posteriorly, with broadly rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Male genitalia A, B Pseudophotopsis subaurea sp. nov., dorsal and ventral views, respectively C, D P. binghami Bischoff, dorsal and ventral views, respectively (modified from Lelej (1985))." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.82.65252.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/537916" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">35D</figureCitation>
). (
<bibRefCitation author="Bischoff, H" journalOrPublisher="Revue d'Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" refId="B7" refString="Bischoff, H, 1920. Monographie der Mutilliden Afrikas [part]. Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 86A (1/3): 1-480." title="Monographie der Mutilliden Afrikas [part]. Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 86 A (1 / 3): 1 - 480." year="1920">Bischoff 1920</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, AS" journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" refId="B25" refString="Lelej, AS, 1985. The Velvet Ants (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae) of the USSR and Neighbouring Countries. Nauka, Leningrad" title="The Velvet Ants (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae) of the USSR and Neighbouring Countries." year="1985">Lelej 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
